DRB-Hicom, KNM, Lion, MWE, Prestar: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-04T00:45:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/drb-hicom-knm-lion-mwe-prestar-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 0.5 percent to
1,506.88.        DRB-Hicom Bhd. (DRB)  : The Employees Provident Fund,
Malaysia’s biggest pension fund, sold 5.6 million shares in the
auto assembler, a stock exchange filing showed. DRB-Hicom was
unchanged at 1.73 ringgit.    KNM Group Bhd. (KNMG)  : The oil and gas services provider
said it has secured new orders amounting to 693 million ringgit
($229 million) so far this year, in line with the “improved
sentiment” in the global industry, according to a company
statement. KNM’s current order-book is 6.4 billion ringgit, KNM
said. The shares climbed 2.6 percent to 2.40 ringgit.        Lion Diversified Holdings Bhd. (LDHB)  : The investment
group said it agreed to form a joint venture with two other
companies,  Lion Forest Industries Bhd. (POS)   and Lion
Industries Corp. (LLB MK), to undertake a blast furnace project
costing $1.06 billion, according to a company statement. Lion
Diversified rose 3.7 percent to 42.5 sen. Lion Industries added
0.6 percent to 1.68 ringgit and Lion Forest was unchanged at
1.79 ringgit.        MWE Holdings Bhd. (MWE)  : The yarn and fabric
manufacturer will earn 6 million ringgit from the sale of shares
in MWE Advanced Structure Sdn., the company said in a statement.
MWE added 0.8 percent to 1.21 ringgit.        Prestar Resources Bhd. (PRST)  : The hardware and tool
manufacturer said it has set up a company in Indonesia to trade
steel materials, according to a company statement. Prestar
shares were unchanged at 42.5 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
